30/03/2007
PODGORICA, Montenegro -- US President George W. Bush has certified that Montenegro is co-operating with Washington in the field of security and defence, clearing the way for US funding. State Department official Christopher Hoh announced the decision on Thursday (March 29th) in Podgorica. He voiced confidence that Montenegro's future is in NATO. 
In other news Thursday, Montenegrin President Filip Vujanovic met with a delegation from the Serbian Democratic Party (DSS), led by DSS deputy chairman Simonida Kordic. They discussed the post-election situation in Serbia, particularly DSS participation in negotiations to form a new democratic government. (Pobjeda, Vijesti - 30/03/07; MINA, RTRS - 29/03/07) 
